Set up

You should already have the processed GC data so it should be contained in a csv file named ppms_###-###.csv where the numbers refer to the machine sample numbers on the GC (not the exetainer sample numbers!). Read in all of the gc ppm data to merge with sample information, because the data you are looking for may span multiple files. Each of the csv files has gc samples that use their own calibration curve.

ppmfiles <- list.files()[grep("ppms_", list.files())]
ppmdata <- lapply(ppmfiles, read_csv)
gc_data <- do.call(rbind, ppmdata)

First save the field data sheet that contains the information about the sample in each exetainer. Put the name of the file here.

sample_info_file <- "Methane Field Data - 06-Oct-2017.csv"

Read in that file from the appropriate location. It should be saved in the Delmarva/GC/field_data folder.

path <- "/nfs/khondula-data/Delmarva/GC"
sample_info <- read_csv(file.path(path, "field_data", sample_info_file))

This is all the data about the samples.

sample_info %<>% arrange(Exetainer_ID)

Chamber samples

Identify the samples associated with chamber sampling from the Method column in the field data sheet.

chamb <- filter(sample_info, Method %in% c("SC", "FC"))

Merge with gc_data to add ppm data (and CO2 peak areas). The gc_data object has info about all of the samples but joining it with the chamb data frame will only take the ppm data from the samples of interest.

chamb %<>% left_join(gc_data, by = c("Exetainer_ID" = "exetainer_ID")) %>%
  dplyr::select(-precis100, -precis1000, -Notes -Sample_description)

Make a new column with just the timepoint and not replicate samples

chamb$tpoint <- substr(chamb$Timepoint, 1,2)

Number of samples

How many samples were taken at each chamber at each timepoint?

chamb_summary <- chamb %>% 
  group_by(Site, Method, Chamber_ID, tpoint) %>%
  summarise(number_samples = n()) %>%
  spread(tpoint, number_samples)
kable(chamb_summary, caption = "Number of samples per timepoint at each chamber")

Plots

barplot

Barplot showing ppm values for each sample by timepoint and site

sc1 <- chamb %>% group_by(Site, Method, Chamber_ID, tpoint) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = tpoint, y = ch4_ppm, col = tpoint, group = Timepoint)) +
  geom_bar(colour="black", stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(), aes(fill = tpoint)) +
  scale_y_log10() + facet_grid(Site~Chamber_ID) +
  theme(legend.position="none") +
  geom_text(aes(label = signif(ch4_ppm, 3)), 
            color = "black", size = 2.5, 
            position = position_dodge(width = 1),
            vjust = -.5)
sc1
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_bar).
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_text).

boxplot

sc2 <- chamb %>% group_by(Site, Method, Chamber_ID, tpoint) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = tpoint, y = ch4_ppm, col = tpoint)) +
  geom_boxplot(colour="black", aes(fill = tpoint)) +
  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, geom="point", shape=5, size=3) +
  scale_y_log10() + facet_grid(Site~Chamber_ID) +
  theme(legend.position="none")
sc2

line graphs

chamb_avgs <- chamb %>% group_by(Site, Method, Chamber_ID, tpoint, Time) %>%
  summarise(ch4_ppm_avg = mean(ch4_ppm, na.rm = TRUE))

chamb_avgs %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Time, y = ch4_ppm_avg, col = Chamber_ID)) +
  # geom_point() + 
  # geom_line() + 
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~Site, scales = "free") +
  scale_y_log10() +
  geom_point(data = chamb, aes(x = Time, y = ch4_ppm))
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

CO2 peaks

chamb %>% group_by(Site, Method, Chamber_ID) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Time, y = CO2peak, col = Chamber_ID)) +
  geom_point() + geom_line() + facet_wrap(~Site, scales = "free")
